Collection Framework / API
	- Provides implementation of well known data structures in the industry
	- Builds on generic
	- Called as Collection because the root interface name is collection
	- Java's Optimized implementation of DS so the developers can focus on business
Collection(Interface)
	- List
	- Set
		-SortedSet
	- Queue
	-Dequeue
	-Map
		-SortedMap

Collection
	-Collection of objects, one object per element/node
List
	- Sequence is guaranteed, duplicates are allowed
	- ArrayList, LinkedList, Vector(Synchronized)
Set
	- Sequence not guaranteed, duplicates are not allowed
	- HashSet
SortedSet
	- Maintains Order
	- TreeSet
Map
	- 2 Objects per node/element,represents key value pair, duplicate keys are not allowed
	- HashMap, HashTable(Synchronized), Properties, ResourceBundle, ConcurrentHashMap
SortedMap
	- keys are maintained in order
	- TreeMap
	
Traversing over Collection
	- Using for loop over index (Works with list types of Collection)
	- Iterators was most commonly used way, ListIterator allows bi-directional traversing.
	- For-each is used most commonly today
	- forEach() method is newer addition
	
i18n - Internationalization


Book
	- isbn
	- author
	- title
	- price
	
pojo - plain old java object
Dao  - data access object

Layered Architecture
- Presentation Layer
	- User Interface (GUI/CLI/Web UI)
- Business Logic
	- Business rules in service classes
- Persistence Layer
	- CRUD Operations (DAO/JDBC/JPA)
	
	
Injections
	- Constructor Injection
	- Setter Injection